            "tol": 0.000001,
            "explain": "$[\\mathbb{Q}(\\sqrt{2},\\sqrt{3}):\\mathbb{Q}]=4$, and if $\\theta$ is primitive then $[\\mathbb{Q}(\\theta):\\mathbb{Q}]=4$, so $m_\\theta$ has degree $4$ (explicitly $x^4-10x^2+1$)."
