            "explain": "$13=2^2+3^2=3^2+2^2$, giving the $8$ signed ordered pairs $(\\pm 2,\\pm 3),(\\pm 3,\\pm 2)$. This is $r_2(13)=8$, consistent with Jacobi's formula $4(d_1-d_3)=4(2-0)=8$."
